    <h2>Anchor Tag (a)</h2>

    <p>
        The <b>a</b> tag is used to create hyperlinks that connect a web page to another section on the same webpage,
        another webpage, or allow a user to upload or download a file.
    </p>

    <p>
        The <b>a</b> tag uses the <b>href</b> attribute to specify the destination that the user will be taken to when the link is clicked.
        A hyperlink can be text, an image, or even a video.
    </p>

    <h4>General Syntax of the Anchor Tag</h4>

    <pre>
&lt;a href="Destination"&gt;Target Destination&lt;/a&gt;
    </pre>

    <p>
