    <h2>HTML Lists</h2>

    <p>
        A list is a sequence of items arranged in order. Lists help organize content so that information
        becomes clearer and easier to read.
    </p>

    <p>
        HTML supports three types of lists:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Ordered List</li>
        <li>Unordered List</li>
        <li>Definition List</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Ordered List</h3>

    <p>
        In an ordered list, the sequence of items is labeled using numbers, letters (A, B, C),
        or Roman numerals.
    </p>

    <p><em><b>Task:</b> Create a list of 5 common HTML tags.</em></p>

    <ol type="i">
        <li>Anchor Tag</li>
        <li>Form Tag</li>
        <li>Table Tag</li>
        <li>Div Tag</li>
        <li>Image Tag</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Unordered List</h3>

    <p>
        An unordered list uses bullet points to list items.
    </p>

